bio.experienceSummary: I am a nanny, teacher, house manager, artist, and musician. I am Montessori trained and have 18 years of experience. I tutor, mentor, and babysit. I have worked with children ranging from newborn to 15 including special needs. When they help make their food, garden, or have fun eating their lunch it is easy to create healthy eating habits at any age. It is important to incorporate art, music, science, language, food, nature, and creativity into every aspect of learning. I strive to teach them why and how we do things. It is our job to nurture while educating so that they know how to be compassionate, self aware, socially adjusted, kind, and selfless adults. I facilitate their growth with teaching Spanish, exploration, nature, imagination, many types of physical activity, reading and adventure. I am CPR/First Aid certified. Every child has their own personality and needs so customize my approach. I can't wait to meet your little ones.

description.originalText:
Shina is the real deal. She was our nanny for 4 and a half years and it's clear she knows her stuff. From day 1, she was on top of everything, always bringing a blend of professional commitment and warmth to our home. She's got a knack for understanding kids and what they need; she could write a how-to book on nannying/babysitting.

What really makes Shina stand out is how she connects with kids of all ages, from babies to grade-schoolers and older. During her time with us, our kids didn't just get older - they really grew as individuals. We had to say goodbye because our kids are now too old for a nanny, but Shina's impact will last their whole lives. She's a genuinely kind person full of good ideas, boundless energy, and a foundational love for kids.

bio.experienceSummary:
I have extensive experienced caring for children since I was a teenager. I am a 50-year-old mother of two young adults. I am a preschool Director in a Spanish Immersion school in Candler Park, Atlanta b
I'm currently a Spanish tutor in the evenings.

I have cared for newborns to 12-year-olds and anything in between. I have experienced with Autistic and Down Syndrome children. Plenty of references. I'm Spanish native speaker. Born in Buenos Aires, Argentina. I'm also a Textile Designer with a studio where I teach Fiber Arts on the weekends.

Fully vaccinated and boosted.

Hi! I'm Ana, I'm 28 and I'd describe myself as reliable, patient and loving. I'm looking for a long term position. I have worked as a babysitter for 5 years, taking care of new borns to up to 12 years old. My most recent experience was with a 4mo boy.

I'm comfortable working with multiple children, meal prep and light housekeeping towards the kids.

I have also taught English and Science for 4 years, for kids of all ages. I speak fluent English and Portuguese and intermediate Spanish.

I am CPR certified and first aid trained. I have lots of experience with kids in the spectrum. I'm a strong driver with a clean record. I'm fully vaccinated and I love all kinds of animals!

If you liked me please reach out!
Hello! My name is Marie ! I love working with kids and spending my time outdoors. I am home from college for the summer and are looking for a babysitting/nannying job.

My name is Teleah M and I have 4 years experience in babysitting/nannying. I am energetic and can be active and play with the kids. I also am very intelligent and can help the kids with homework or make sure they don't lose what they learned over the summer. I also have my own car and can provide transportation to and from activities, school, and home. If necessary I can bring games or activites as well. I also can do some tidying around the house and cook. I have taken multiple cooking classes in different countries like Spain, Peru, China, Italy and more. I also speak some Chinese and can help with elemetary level Chinese tutoring. SO if ou're looking for a well trained, bubbly, responsible nanny, I'm you're girl.

I love spending time with kids and have experience in multiple realms. I've worked with infants to 18-year-olds! I'm majoring in Social work and I love what I get out of working with kids , the care they show you, the memories , and always the nicest compliments. I'm the oldest of 3 so I'm always looking out for the little ones! I've been a Nanny 3 other times as well as other baby sitting gigs. I have references and my own transportation so don't hesitate to ask!! Thank you for considering me!

Hi, there! I'm Taylor! 

Throughout the years, I've loved working with children. Starting when I was a teenager, I worked with daycare, after-school programs, and occasional babysitting jobs. As I've gotten older, I've directed and counseled at outdoors-centered summer camps. Most recently, I nannied for a year+ for a family with 4 children, 7 and younger.

I'm a jack of all trades (I know a little bit about a lot of stuff!), and am a quick learner. The family I last cared for required tasks ranging from childcare (of course), to house management, cooking, and more. I very much consider myself part of the family team, so I'm happy to assist wherever I'm needed!

My personal interests include gardening, cooking, music, and photography. I also speak intermediate French, so if your kids need any help with their language homework, I'm happy to assist! I adore kids (and pets!) of all ages, and would love to get to know your family and help however I can!

description.displayText: Our family of 6 (children ages 7, 5, 4, and 2, one being on the autism spectrum) were very fortunate be under the care of Ms. Taylor full time for a year and a half. It is easy to see at first, her positive personality. She is an open communicator and follows through with tasks and responsibilities. With the children, her patience can't be matched. She has a tool box filled with behavior management techniques and entertainment ideas. She is open and willing to learn new tactics to help children overcome new obstacles. On top of being great with the kids, Ms. Taylor has an array of skills from cooking to handiwork around the house. She is a problem solver and always ready to tackle anything that pops up. In all, Ms. Taylor is a positive, reliable, and very capable nanny. Any family would be very lucky to have her and we can't recommend more.

bio.experienceSummary:
I'd describe my personality as friendly, positive, organized.

I like working with kids because they are full of adventure, and we as adults can learn something from them.

I'm looking for a part time job.

I started working with kids when I was 15, I was babysitting, I've worked as a Lifegaurd. I have been a volunteer EMT for the past 6 years, regularly working with kids and teaching trainings.

In my spare time, I like to hike, cook, read, act in theatrical productions.

description.originalText: An older woman fell down at a restaurant, and I saw Bridget race to her aid in seconds; stabilizing her neck and attending to her wounds. She checked for concussion and pulse and calmed the lady’s family until local paramedics arrive.  She was amazing and cool under pressure. Bridget is an EMT/paramedic herself.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi there! I'm a seasoned babysitter/nanny with a knack for being the trustworthy, responsible, and nurturing caregiver your family needs. I'm currently the go-to for 10 wonderful families, but I'm always excited to welcome more into the fold!
Please reach out to inquire of availability.

description.originalText: I had an excellent experience with Taylor! She was punctual, kind, and very attentive to my daughters’ needs. My daughters absolutely loved spending time with her and felt very comfortable. She went above and beyond, engaging them in fun activities and even helped me personally when I needed it. I felt completely at ease knowing my daughters were in such caring and capable hands. I would highly recommend Taylor to anyone looking for a reliable and trustworthy babysitter!

bio.experienceSummary:
I'm a senior chemistry major in college hoping to become a clinical psychologist after graduating. I have experience babysitting a wide range of ages and love to help with homework especially anything involving math or chemistry! I love doing art with kids and just studied art and architecture in Europe for the last semester. I am currently getting a yoga teacher training certificate so love to teach kids about yoga and the power of mindfulness!

I'd describe my personality as organized, kind, and cheerful!

I like working with kids because they have a different perspective on the world. I love hearing about their thoughts and learning from them. I also find it super rewarding to see them grow as a people! 

I'm looking for a job that lets me get to know the kids and family. 

I started working with kids when I was 13. 

My skills include baking/cooking, cleaning, crafting, and driving. I have First-Aid and CPR training but unfortunately have not been able to renew it this year.
